
1/ Create the field map : 
gfortran -o geneSectorMap geneSectorMap.f 
./geneSectorMap

map is stored in geneSectorMap.out


2/ Run sector360deg.dat :

zgoubi -in sector360deg.dat

results are in zgoubi.res

3/ It is possible to list field vs. X in zgoubi.res:

set IL=1 in input .dat file : 

 'TOSCA'                                                                                                      5
0  1


3/ It is possible to plot trajectories, for instance using zpop (or gnuplot, reading zgoubi.plt) : 

set IL=2 in input .dat file : 

 'TOSCA'                                                                                                      5
0  2

See example in sector360deg_XY.eps, a graphic obtained using zpop



